\pard\f0\fs28 Annuals to perennials. Leaves entire to pinnatipartite. Sepals erecto-patent; petals clawed, usually yellow. Gynophore usually short. Fruit an elongate, linear siliqua with a short beak; valves compressed, with a prominent median vein. Seeds usually in 2 rows in each loculus, ovoid or ellipsoidal. (Incl.{\i  Pendulina} Willk.)
