\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. D. harra} (Forskål) Boiss.,{\i  Fl. Or. }{\b 1}: 388 (1867) (incl.{\i  Pendulina intricata }Willk.,{\i  P. webbiana} Willk.,{\i  P. hispida} auct. hisp.). Subglaucous, more or less fleshy, suffruticose perennial, glabrous or hispid. Lower leaves toothed, lobed or pinnatipartite, the lobes entire or toothed. Petals 6-10 mm, bright yellow. Siliqua 12-60 × 1·8-3 mm; gynophore 2·5-7 mm, conspicuous. 2n = 26.{\i  W. Mediterranean region.} Hs Si.
